      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-strung S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit delivers a linear power band with peak torque arriving at 4,900 RPM, benefiting from a recent comprehensive VANOS overhaul and valve shim adjustment. The 6-speed Getrag manual transmission shifts with tactile precision, paired with a limited-slip differential that ensures optimal torque distribution. Crucially, the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates to address floor pan fatigue, maintaining structural lateral rigidity. The suspension utilizes refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers, preserving the original kinematics while sharpening turn-in response. Though the finish reflects honest road use, the drivetrain is synchronized for peak performance.",
